git commands
============

> [To View only files changed, not the diff in each file]
		git show --pretty="format:" --name-only 5c5b389

> [Create a bundle and clone it else where to preserve the .git directory]
        git bundle create kernel.bundle --all

        >> [copy it where ever u want and..]
            git clone kernel.bundle
> [Try this]
        git diff --staged

> [Diff of untracked files]
        [git add -N or --intent-to-add, records only the fact that the path will be added later]
	        git add -N arch/arm/boot/dts/overlays/tlv320aic32x4-codec-overlay.dts
	        git diff

> git config --global color.ui true

> [ Remove commit msg and keep the files added in staging area ]
		git reset --soft HEAD~

> [ Remove a file after git ADD/COMMIT]
		git reset HEAD -- <file-to-exclude>

> [ Update a Github forked repository ]
		git remote add upstream https://github.com/original-repo.git
		git fetch upstream
		git checkout master
		git rebase upstream/master

	[ Commit it back to your own forked repository ]
			git push -f origin master

> [ Rebasing your changes on top of the current master ]
		git checkout new-feature-branch
		git rebase master
		git checkout master
		git merge new-feature-branch

> [ Deleting a branch ]
		git branch -D new-feature-branch

> [Format Patch]
		[Get 3 patches from the HEAD, including the HEAD]
			git format-patch -3 -o /tmp/

> [Compare changes from your branch vs remote branch]
		git diff origin/rpi-4.14.y rpi-4.14.y

		[Names of files changed only]
			git diff --name-status origin/rpi-4.14.y

> [There is no tracking information for the current branch.]
		git pull https://kernel.googlesource.com/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux master

> [Adding a repository into github]
		echo "# rpi-things" >> README.md
		git init
		git add README.md
		git commit -m "first commit"
		git remote add origin git@github.com:b-ak/rpi-things.git
		git push -u origin master

> [Rebasing]
		[Case study with RPi Kernel patches]
		9ef83cb5fd44 (HEAD -> rpi-4.14.y, origin/rpi-4.14.y, origin/HEAD) configs: Add CONFIG_SND_AUDIOSENSE_PI=m
		e3952f879cf5 BCM270X: Adding device tree support for AudioSense-Pi add-on soundcard
		45b10f4c61ce ASoC: Add support for AudioSense-Pi add-on soundcard
		a0911976a873 (upstream/rpi-4.14.y) Merge remote-tracking branch 'stable/linux-4.14.y' into rpi-4.14.y

		[Need to edit 45b10f4c61ce and commit it back to upstream]
			git rebase --interactive a0911976a873
				[
				 pick 45b10f4c61ce ASoC: Add support for AudioSense-Pi add-on soundcard
				 pick e3952f879cf5 BCM270X: Adding device tree support for AudioSense-Pi add-on soundcard
				 pick 9ef83cb5fd44 configs: Add CONFIG_SND_AUDIOSENSE_PI=m
				]

			Modify "pick" to "edit" in the line whose commit you want to modify. Hit :wq
				[
				 edit 45b10f4c61ce ASoC: Add support for AudioSense-Pi add-on soundcard
				 pick e3952f879cf5 BCM270X: Adding device tree support for AudioSense-Pi add-on soundcard
				 pick 9ef83cb5fd44 configs: Add CONFIG_SND_AUDIOSENSE_PI=m
				]

		[Make your changes and then commit them]
			git commit --amend

		[Return back to the previous head commit]
			git rebase --continue

		[Push the changes]
			git push -f origin rpi-4.14.y

> [Stashing]
		[Create a stash]
			git stash save "def_config_changes"

		[See the list]
			git stash list

		[Apply the latest stash and delete it]
			git stash pop

		[Apply the stash and keep the stash]
			git stash apply stash@{0}

		[Remove the stash]
			git stash drop stash@{0}


converting video to mp3 - avconv video converter
================================================
sudo apt-get install libavcodec-extra libav-tools
avconv -i video.mp4 -b 256K audio.mp3

Multiple lines into one line
----------------------------

		ls -1 | paste -sd " " -
		ls -1 | tr '\n' ' '
		ls -m

for looping for batch processing
--------------------------------
for input in *.mp4; do avconv -i "$input" -b 256K "${input}.mp3"; done

vim
===

> [ delete all trailing whitespace (at the end of each line)]
		:%s/\s\+$//gc

> [ Replace "( " with "(" ]
		:.,$s/( /(/gc

> [ Replace "+=" with " += " ]
		:.,$s/+=/ += /gc

> [ Remove all lines starting with {pattern} ]
		:%s/{pattern}.*//gc
			|		|
			 #define

> [ Replace all occurances of string ]
		:%s/old/new/gc

> [ Replace all occurances within a range ]
		:31,57s/old/new/gc

> [ Converting tabs to spaces ]
		:set tabstop=4 shiftwidth=4 expandtab
		:retab

> [ Convert space to tab ]
		:set noexpandtab
		:retab!


setting up cscope
==================

find `pwd` -name "*.c" -o -name "*.h" -o -name "*.S" > cscope.files
cscope -q -R -b -i cscope.files
mkdir ~/.vim/plugin

> create cscope_maps.vim
  Download cscope_maps.vim and copy to ~/.vim/plugin/cscope_maps.vim
  Remove all trailing white spaces in the file

In ~/.bashrc
       export CSCOPE_DB=<path-to-cscope.out>/cscope.out
In ~/.vimrc
       cs add $CSCOPE_DB


It should work right away..
Ctrl+\ s – Find String
Ctrl+\ g – Find global definition
Ctrl+\ d – Find functions called by this function
etc etc etc

If it doesn't check stack overflow favorites for debugging techniques.

Wget
====
-U will send a "User-Agent"
for i in {01..96}; do wget -U firefox "http://www.impactscan.org/slides/xrayct/img0${i}.gif"; done

> [Recursively fetch a directory]
	wget --user-agent="User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.9; rv:32.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/32.0" --recursive --no-parent --reject "index.html*" --accept "*.mkv" http://blah-blah/one/two/abc/s01/

> [Resume an interrupted download]
	wget --user-agent="User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.9; rv:32.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/32.0" -c -r --no-parent --reject "index.html*" -A "*.mkv" http://blah-blah/one/two/abc/s01/

> [Get from links]
	wget -c --user-agent="User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.9; rv:32.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/32.0" -i links

