chown
=====

> Change the file so it is owned by root
	sudo chown root:root /etc/systemd/system/tightvncserver.service

tar
===

> Extract the file in the specified directory (ex: /usr/local)
       tar -C /usr/local -xzf go1.5.1.linux-amd64.tar.gz

> Extract Linux kernel
       tar -Jxvf linux-4.2.3.tar.xz

> Create multiple tar files
	Compress into multi 1MB volumes
	○  tar -cvzf - root | split --bytes=1m --suffix-length=4 --numeric-suffix - root.tar.gz
	
	Uncompress using 
	○  cat root.tar.* | tar xvzf -




kill
====
> Find and kill gedit
       ps aux | grep gedit | grep -v grep | awk '{print $2}' | xargs kill
or
       pkill gedit
or
       kill -9 `pidof gedit`

